Description: Fragment of pottery transport amphora. Flattened handle at neck join, downturning. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light red-brown, hard fired.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p..173, 10). Probably from same die as Athenian Agora SS14430. Fabric very different from the piece with a name perhaps in Ournio- or Thurnio-, British Museum 1925,0119.453.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1611)
